Package: StatINLA
Title: Interactive Bayesian Spatial and Spatio-Temporal Modeling with INLA
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-07-08
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Manuel",
           family = "Spinola",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mspinola10@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7839-1908"))
Description: An interactive and didactic Shiny application for applied Bayesian
    spatial and spatio-temporal modeling using Integrated Nested Laplace
    Approximation (INLA) via the inlabru package. Covers log-Gaussian Cox
    process models for point pattern data, SPDE spatial random fields,
    spatio-temporal extensions, and integrated species distribution models
    combining presence-only and presence-absence data sources such as GBIF
    and eBird. Part of the StatSuite ecosystem, ICOMVIS, Universidad
    Nacional, Costa Rica.
